HEADWORD: ginep
<hw>ginep</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A tropical American tree
(<spn>Melicocca bijuga</spn>) bearing a small edible fruit with green
leathery skin and sweet juicy translucent pulp.</def> <altsp>[Also
spelled <asp>genip</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Spanish lime, Spanish lime tree, honey berry,
mamoncillo, <spn>Melicocca bijuga</spn>, <spn>Melicoccus
bijugatus</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ging</ent>⟦br⟧
